Civilization builds walls.

Pirates build horizons.

Perhaps that is why we never forget them.

---

Kings promise safety.

Ports promise order.

Laws promise peace.

And yetâ€”

somewhere inside every soul

a small voice whispers:

Run.

---

Pirates are not criminals.

Not really.

They are questions.

What if the map is wrong?

What if the crown lies?

What if freedom waits beyond the last lighthouse?

So we return to the sea again and again.

Through books.

Through stories.

Through dreams.

Because the ocean represents the one thing history cannot cageâ€”

possibility.

---

Maybe we do not read pirate tales to escape.

Maybe we read them to remember

who we almost were

before fear taught us obedience.

And somewhere far away,

a ship still sails.

Waiting.

